  "narrative": {
    "intro": "Federal contract obligations for NAICS 541690, Other Scientific and Technical Consulting Services, total $1.2B in FY2026 to date, with 2,253 awards and an average award size of $512K. Obligations are down 46.7% year over year, and current-year totals are partial (fiscal year to date). Historical obligations show larger annual totals in prior years: FY21 $1.9B, FY22 $2B, FY23 $2B, FY24 $2.3B, and FY25 $2.2B. The FY2026 to date total of $1.2B reflects a smaller share of prior full-year spending. The Department of Defense is the largest buyer in FY2026 to date at $388M, followed by Agency for International Development at $276M and Department of Health and Human Services at $240M. On the vendor side, a large undisclosed group listed as DOMESTIC AWARDEES (UNDISCLOSED) accounts for $275M, with GENERAL DYNAMICS ONE SOURCE LLC at $78.5M and KELLY SERVICES, INC. at $59.1M. These figures describe the market size, top buyers, and top suppliers through the fiscal year to date.",
